doc.after: The existence and nature of different classes of passenger service on British trains has varied over time From its inception first second and third class carriages were provided alongside luxury Pullman coaches Currently most longer distance services offer first class and standard class service while most local and suburban services are single class as are urban transit services such as the London Underground
